The paper deals with image reconstruction using a modified convolutional neural network architecture, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses the challenge of sparsely sampled data, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT). The use of neural networks for image reconstruction is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves optimizing the network architecture, which is a topic in neural engineering (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which is a subfield of signal processing (cs.SI).
